post_text: Congratulations Whitney!
shared_text:
American Farmers & Ranchers Youth Program
June 22 at 7:00 PM ¬∑

Introducing Whitney Glazier as a state scholarship recipient! Glazier's agent is Delvin Jech. Glazier has participated in both the AFR Speech contest and AFR Ag Achievement contest and attended the AFR Youth Leadership Summit. After graduating from vet school, Glazier plans to open her own large animal clinic in rural Oklahoma.

"I have been able to attend the Leadership Summit the past several years," Glazier said. "This has led to the development of team building and leadership skills that are all invaluable in all career paths and community endeavors in my future."
text:
Congratulations Whitney!

American Farmers & Ranchers Youth Program
June 22 at 7:00 PM ¬∑

Introducing Whitney Glazier as a state scholarship recipient! Glazier's agent is Delvin Jech. Glazier has participated in both the AFR Speech contest and AFR Ag Achievement contest and attended the AFR Youth Leadership Summit. After graduating from vet school, Glazier plans to open her own large animal clinic in rural Oklahoma.

"I have been able to attend the Leadership Summit the past several years," Glazier said. "This has led to the development of team building and leadership skills that are all invaluable in all career paths and community endeavors in my future."

2020 Senior Spotlight
Riley Freelanderüë®‚Äçüéì

Nickname: Free

‚ÄúI have 4 siblings, Addison, Elizabeth, Eleanor, and Caleb‚Äù

My Hobbies: Programming and video games

My plans after high school: To get certifications and obtain a successful career in the IT field

Extra-curricular activities: Robotics, Basketball and Track

My favorite elementary memory: ‚ÄúRoller skating around the gym with my friends‚Äù

Favorite JH memory: ‚ÄúExperiencing high school for the first time and exploring all of the responsibilities that came with it‚Äù

Favorite HS memory: Building a robot which was ‚Äúaccidently overpowered‚Äù and almost shattered someone‚Äôs phone.

What I will miss most after high school: MY FRIENDS

If I could travel anywhere: ‚ÄúI would go to California to see the giant red wood trees‚Äù

The class I enjoyed the most at LHS: ‚ÄúHistory Classes‚Äù

What 3 words best describes me: Smart, Nice, Respectful

What advice would I leave to the freshman: ‚ÄúKeep your grades up, trust me I know from experience, it‚Äôs better that way‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.

Great job!!

post_text: The Lomega Senior Class attended ‚ÄúReality Check‚Äù provided by Kingfisher County OSU Extension Office. The students were given a career, relationship status (Single/Married and kids/no kids), and a monthly gross and net salary. Booths included in the event - Banking, Transportation, Car Insurance, Car Tag & Taxes, Housing, Utilities, Medical/Dental/Life Insurance, Clothing, Furniture, Entertainment, and etc. If they had money left over in their monthly budget, they received a Payday candy bar and no money leftover they received a Zero candy bar. It was such a GREAT EVENT!!

Lomega Stakeholders Poll

To participate in the poll, please click on the following link:

https://forms.gle/JEp6Xq2jsGtsumZr7

To: Parents/Guardians of LHS Juniors

9/16/2019

Lomega High School is communicating with parents/guardians of students who will participate in the CCRA junior state testing program this school year.

Our school district plans to administer the ACT test in the spring on April 7 to all eligible juniors as part of the state contract with the Oklahoma State Department of Education and ACT.

Since most Oklahoma colleges and many colleges in surrounding states use the ACT score for basis of admission, our district feels this is an excellent opportunity for juniors to take this test with no cost to them or their families.

Should you have any questions/comments, please feel free to email me before November, 2019.

Thank You!

Tracy Shiever
Counselor
Lomega High School
405-729-4281
tracy@lomega.k12.ok.us

March 26, 2019 at 9:40 AM ¬∑

Four Chisholm Trail Technology Center students recently qualified for the Business Professionals of America Spring Leadership Conference competitive events held in Tulsa, March 11-13. The CTTC qualifiers included, front, Lomega High School students Jessica Mather, state qualifier in database applications and Kelly Russell, state qualifier in digital publishing. Also competing were Kingfisher High School students Hayden Wittrock, back, placing fifth in database applications and Logan Hightower, state qualifier in computer repair and troubleshooting. These students represented the Digital Technologies and Computer Repair Networking programs at CTTC.
